<h2>Results</h2>
<section>
  <p>
    You took {{pluralize stepsForward "step"}} forward and {{pluralize stepsBack "step"}} back for a total score of <b>{{parentModel.score}}</b>.
    <br/>
    The higher your score, the more privilege you are afforded.
  </p>
  <ScoreBar @score={{parentModel.score}} />
  <h4>How Your Score Compares With Others:</h4>
  <p>
    The average score is <b>{{averageScore}}</b>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Below are scores from other respondents. Positive scores are shown in green while negative scores are shown in red.
  </p>
</section>
<section>
  {{#each model as |answer|}}
    <ScoreBar @score={{answer.score}} />
  {{/each}}
</section>
<section>
  <p>
    A privilege walk is merely one of many tools to examine one's privilege in society. Learn more about the <a href="https://www.albany.edu/ssw/efc/pdf/Module%205_1_Privilege%20Walk%20Activity.pdf">classroom activity</a> and some of the <a href="https://medium.com/@MegB/why-i-dont-won-t-facilitate-privilege-walks-anymore-and-what-i-do-instead-380c95490e10">criticisms</a> of privilege walks.
  </p>
</section>
